align=left class=m><span class=title>   Shades of a Nightmare Pt. 1</span><hr size=1> I know you guys hate this, but this story is a work in progress, and looks like it is going to be a long one.  So, I apologize in advance for breaking it up.<br>
<br>
&quot;Iiiee!  What me tell you?  What me tell you again?  Uou bad girl!  Go, you no Shamaness! You only da bad mojo!&quot;<br>
<br>
Gkako slowly walked home, now she would have to tell her Da and Ma that she had been kicked out of the Shaman guild.  She knew they wouldn't understand.  Her Da, well he was a Basher, and he always complained that talking to her made pains come in his head.  <br>
<br>
Her Ma was the daughter of a great Shamaness, but it seemed the talent had skipped her Ma, and twisted itself in her.<br>
<br>
Gkako didn't understand it.  She knew she could work de mojo, she could feel it in her, but the words were wrong.<br>
<br>
&quot;Gkako, she tell you go?  You no be back now!&quot;  Ghunk said to her, he had been in the Shaman guild with her, they were the same age, as far as they knew.  They had always known each other, and were good friends.  Ghunk even helped her alot with her Shaman studies.  &quot;Me see, her cloak, poof!  Dat fire be hot!&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Ghunk, me no want fire.  Me want da wolfie feets, but me gots fire.&quot;  Gkako sighed, unsure of what her future held.  She didn't want to be a merchant!  Selling boring things to the same people she had seen all her life.  She wanted more, and thought that being a Shaman, would help her do that.<br>
<br>
&quot;Gkako, yous good wif da bashin, meebee you go be Basher, like you da!&quot;  Ghunk said excitedly, he had wanted to be a Basher, until the Shamans saw he had the mojo.<br>
<br>
&quot;But, mes feel mojo!  Da no have mojo, me use mojo, me bash!  Me talk to Hukulk.  Me goes to Nightkeep!&quot;  The possibilities went through Gkako's head so fast it began to hurt, never in her life had she had so many thoughts that all made sense.  She saw herself sneaking through sewers in far off Qeynos, and riding boats to the lands of the puny races.<br>
<br>
&quot;You no Shadow Knight!&quot;  Ghunk laughed at the idea.  &quot;You no death finger!&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Me have mojo, me good basher.  Me no shaman, me no Basher.  Me *is* Shadow Knight, me *learn* death finger.&quot;  Gkako said desicively.  Knowing for the first time in her life that this was what she wanted.<br>
<br>
So saying, Gkako turned her back on her friend and hunt-mate.  Sh ehad found her Master's voice, and it was the voice of FEAR.<br>
